column5: Have not been out since last wednesday. My gawd,the snow walk is killer. Or maybe getting old is killer.ðŸ¤¯ 	Fish were tight to the bottom under all the herring and smelts. They would come in,but move on by. Finally the bait fish moved along and the it only took 5 min to hook up. One on the meegs , the other on a high hook preg scud I tied. 	Will be in the smoker in the AM.
Nice catch there "B" PS Ya got em cleaned up pretty good LOL

ugh, were dealing with a deep layer of snow slush on 2-3 inches of clear...total nightmare on my home waters making it so that I cant get to where I want to fish. I might try man up and haul my butt through 4 kilometers round trip of the garbage this weekend...but man life would be easier if i could just pop on my sled and get to my spot.
Do not forget where ya put them jigs,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
Lol oh yeah top zipper pocket. I will go check
Same conditions on my lake...can't run my Pioneer more than a few feet without getting bogged down. The Walleye, Whitefish and Crappies are catching a break this winter..

Managed to get a few orders completed this morning as the smoker was doing what it does,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,, Sweet and salty candy,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,  Thursday looks like a good morning to get a few hours in before that cold snap shuts them down. That,s ok, work the weekend and another barometer change come Monday. Just in time for fishing again.
Smoked whitie, my favourite! Supper tonight was moose tortillas, I think a good swap would be them for some smoked whitefish, we need to get together one of these years! Doug
They do look awesome. I suddenly have a craving.
